# shadcn instructions

Use the latest version of Shadcn to install new components, like this command to add a button component:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

# Agent Skills

This project has installed agent skills from [vercel-labs/agent-skills](https://github.com/vercel-labs/agent-skills). The skills are located in the `skills/` directory.

## Available Skills

### react-best-practices

React and Next.js performance optimization guidelines from Vercel Engineering. Contains 40+ rules across 8 categories, prioritized by impact.

**Use when:**
- Writing new React components or Next.js pages
- Implementing data fetching (client or server-side)
- Reviewing code for performance issues
- Optimizing bundle size or load times

**Location:** `skills/react-best-practices/SKILL.md`

### web-design-guidelines

Review UI code for compliance with web interface best practices. Audits your code for 100+ rules covering accessibility, performance, and UX.

**Use when:**
- "Review my UI"
- "Check accessibility"
- "Audit design"
- "Review UX"
- "Check my site against best practices"

**Location:** `skills/web-design-guidelines/SKILL.md`

### vercel-deploy-claimable

Deploy applications and websites to Vercel instantly. No authentication required. Deployments are "claimable" - users can transfer ownership to their own Vercel account.

**Use when:**
- "Deploy my app"
- "Deploy this to production"
- "Push this live"
- "Deploy and give me the link"

**Location:** `skills/vercel-deploy-claimable/SKILL.md`

## Skill Usage

Skills are automatically available once installed. Reference the corresponding SKILL.md file when relevant tasks are detected. For detailed rules and references:

- React performance: See `skills/react-best-practices/references/` for complete documentation
- Web design: Fetch guidelines from the source URL specified in the SKILL.md
- Vercel deploy: Use the script at `skills/vercel-deploy-claimable/scripts/deploy.sh`
